From Tim Clock Subject Re Pease without justice cann't last Re Last Opportunity for Peace In article Godada Shi writes In article RAM VIKASH TIWARY writes Now that all the parties are back to the negotiating table the stakes as I see is are indeed high and the future stability of the region and perhaps the world is in the While Israel continues to refuse to talk to the PLO labelling it a terrorist organisation the window of opportunity for peace is narrowing by the If the present talks are allowed to deadlock without agreement for a long term and lasting peace that taken into account the interest of all involved the chances of peace will indeed The PLO by its decision to rejoin the talks has staked its reputation on the success of the The longer the talks continue and they started and half years ago without any tangible progress the further will the PLO support in the territories If a land for peace agreement can be reached and real soon the chances of a comprehensive peace treaty is The Arabs once and for all recognise Israel's right to exist inside secure borders and Isreal would in turn recognise the legitimate right of the Palestinians to self deternimation and With peace guarantee by air tight treaties the region can then hope to dwell on the economic and social well being of its population rather than prepare for the next Ram Vikash Tiwary As we see right now the position of influence enjoyed by parties favoring the negotiation process is tenuous at The local elections in Hebron that the PLO was expected to win perhaps adding a bit to its flagging position of legitimacy in the eyes of Palestinians and the Middle East have been disrupted by Hamas actions overtly directed towards undermining those and all West Bank The present ruling Israeli Labor coalition seems to be one rather thin political The Palestinian delegation has been reduced from to three to protest Israel lack of seriousness in the talks and refusal to reverse all the deportations Hopefully however each of the parties will begin to learn that just the fact that negotiations are taking place does not mean they are giving anything away to the other side which was is the favorite argument of the rejectionists Let's hope that discusion and inevitable disagreement on major issues leads at the same time to some agreement on smaller interim phase whatever term we prefer steps to be Tim Clock Graduate student UCI tel Department of Politics and Society fax University of California Irvine Home tel Irvine CA